# ===== RESULT JSON (stdout) =====
usage: chemkit fukui [-h] --method {xtb,mopac,dft,hf} [--charge CHARGE]
                     [--mult MULTIPLICITY] [--solvent SOLVENT]
                     [--solvent-model {ddcosmo,cpcm,iefpcm}]
                     [--tier {fast,standard,accurate}]
                     [--functional FUNCTIONAL] [--basis BASIS] [--density-fit]
                     [--out OUT] [--accept-defaults]
                     [--stdout {json,path,none}] [--allow-unconverged]
                     [--verbose VERBOSE] [--cation-mult CATION_MULT]
                     [--anion-mult ANION_MULT] [--no-plot]
                     input

positional arguments:
  input                 Path to input geometry (.xyz, .sdf, .pdb).

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --method {xtb,mopac,dft,hf}
  --charge CHARGE
  --mult MULTIPLICITY, --multiplicity MULTIPLICITY
                        Spin multiplicity 2S+1 (default 1).
  --solvent SOLVENT     Implicit solvent: either a known name (e.g. water,
                        methanol, dmso, hexane) OR a numeric dielectric
                        constant (e.g. 2.0) for a custom solvent. Gas phase if
                        omitted. Note: xtb (ALPB) requires a named solvent — a
                        numeric dielectric needs --method dft, hf, or mopac.
  --solvent-model {ddcosmo,cpcm,iefpcm}
                        PySCF continuum solvation model (DFT/HF only): ddcosmo
                        (default, domain-decomposition COSMO), cpcm (C-PCM),
                        or iefpcm (IEF-PCM). MOPAC uses COSMO and xtb uses
                        ALPB regardless; a non-default value with those
                        methods (and a solvent set) is an error.
  --tier {fast,standard,accurate}
                        DFT tier preset (fast=r2SCAN/def2-SVP,
                        standard=B3LYP/def2-TZVP,
                        accurate=wB97M-V/def2-QZVPP). Ignored unless --method
                        dft.
  --functional FUNCTIONAL
                        DFT functional override, libxc name (e.g. b3lyp, pbe0,
                        wb97x_v, wb97m_v, wb97x-d3bj). Ignored unless --method
                        dft.
  --basis BASIS         Basis-set override for DFT/HF (e.g. def2-tzvp, cc-
                        pvtz). Ignored unless --method dft or --method hf.
  --density-fit         Enable density fitting (the RI/resolution-of-identity
                        approximation to the two-electron integrals) for
                        DFT/HF: ~3-10x faster SCF for a ~0.1-0.8 mEh error.
                        OFF BY DEFAULT — chemkit uses exact four-center
                        integrals (plain RKS/UKS/RHF/UHF, matching a hand-
                        written PySCF run); pass this flag to opt into the RI
                        speedup. Ignored for xtb/mopac.
  --out OUT             Output JSON path. Default: <input-
                        stem>_<task>_<method>.json
  --accept-defaults     Explicitly consent to chemkit's silent defaults for
                        consequential knobs the user did not set (DFT
                        tier=standard -> B3LYP/def2-TZVP; HF basis=def2-tzvp;
                        gas phase when no --solvent). Without this flag, a
                        DFT/HF run that omits those knobs is REFUSED so the
                        level of theory is never chosen silently (calculation-
                        reporting-standards non-negotiable #10).
  --stdout {json,path,none}
                        What to print on stdout. 'json' = full result
                        (default), 'path' = compact one-line pointer to the
                        --out file plus convergence/warnings, 'none' = silent.
                        The --out JSON file is always written either way. Use
                        'path' to keep the full blob out of an agent's context
                        and read back fields with jq.
  --allow-unconverged, --no-gate
                        Downgrade the integrity hard-abort to a stamped
                        warning and exit 0 (result marked status=warning,
                        trustworthy=false, gate_bypassed=true). Use ONLY to
                        inspect a failed geometry (collapsed TS, non-converged
                        opt) — the headline number is NOT trustworthy.
  --verbose VERBOSE     PySCF log verbosity (0=silent .. 4=default rich
                        SCF/opt detail .. 5=debug). Streamed to the live .out
                        log; ignored for xtb/mopac.
  --cation-mult CATION_MULT
                        Multiplicity of the N-1 (cation) state. If omitted,
                        derived from --mult: singlet parent → doublet (M+1),
                        higher-spin parent → M-1. Override for systems where
                        the high-spin N-1 is the ground state.
  --anion-mult ANION_MULT
                        Multiplicity of the N+1 (anion) state. If omitted,
                        derived from --mult: singlet parent → doublet (M+1),
                        higher-spin parent → M-1.
  --no-plot             Skip the PNG bar chart of f+/f-/dual per atom.
